content: Ah, the energy of NYC is back! Just caught the sunset over the Hudson from my apartment balcony. Feels good to be home.
Got an email from a quant trading firm. They're interested in my internship experience. Interview next week. Time to polish my pitch.
Caught up with my old mentor over coffee. Discussed my side project on blockchain for sustainable finance. He's keen to help brainstorm.
Spent the last few days coding a prototype for the blockchain project. Hit a snag with smart contract execution. Need to dive deeper into Solidity.
Took a break from coding. Attended a tech meetup last night. Met some folks from a startup working on AI-driven trading algorithms. Exchanged contacts.
Just turned 22. Reflecting on this past year's journey. Realized how much I've grown, but also how much there is still to learn.
The interview with the quant firm went well. They liked my travel insights. Waiting to hear back. Fingers crossed.
Had a setback with my side project. The smart contract isn't functioning as expected. Might need to rethink the whole approach.
Joined a local coding workshop on AI tools. Learned about TensorFlow. This could really speed up my development process.
Spent the day going through my old trading logs. Noticed a pattern in my losses. Need to adjust my risk management strategy.
Met with my mentor again. He's setting me up with some contacts in the sustainable finance space. Networking is key.
